17/11/2002
ISTANBUL, Turkey -- The 48th annual session of the NATO Parliamentary Assembly (NATO PA) continues Sunday (17 November) in Istanbul. The event, which opened Friday, brought together 300 legislators from over 40 countries including the 19 NATO member countries, 17 NATO PA associate members and several parliamentary observer states. Participants will be reviewing issues related to the proliferation of weapons of mass destruction, terrorist threats and the acceptance of new NATO members at this week's enlargement summit in Prague. (Anadolu Agency, BBC, AFP - 16/11/02; NTV MSNBC, NATO PA website - 15/11/02)
